Market Segmentation: 
The global V2X for automotive market is segmented on the basis of connectivity, offering, communication, propulsion type, technology, unit and vehicle type. The growth amongst these segments will help you analyse meagre growth segments in the industries, and provide the users with valuable market overview and market insights to help them in making strategic decisions for identification of core market applications.
On the basis of connectivity, the V2X for automotive market is segmented into cellular connectivity and DSRC.
On the basis of offering, the V2X for automotive market is segmented into hardware and software.
The V2X for automotive market has also been segmented on the basis of communication into vehicle-to-vehicle (V2V), vehicle-to-infrastructure (V2I), vehicle-to-grid (V2G), vehicle-to-pedestrian (V2P), vehicle-to-cloud (V2C) and vehicle-to-device (V2D).
On the basis of propulsion type, the V2X for automotive market is segmented into electric vehicle and internal combustion engine (ICE) vehicle.
Based on technology, the V2X for automotive market is segmented into automated driver assistance, intelligent traffic systems, emergency vehicle notification, passenger information system, fleet and asset management, parking management system, line of sight, non-line of sight, backing and others.
On the basis of unit, the V2X for automotive market is segmented into on-board unit (OBU), roadside unit (RSU).
Based on vehicle type, the V2X for automotive market is segmented into passenger car and commercial vehicle.
